    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok i'll turn off the breaker. i checked it and it looks fine, no swelling or anything. but whenever i turn the power back on, i hear this weird intermittent clicking or static-y sound like the electricity is struggling to flow. it's almost like there's some kind of glitch in the connection even though everything looks clean. any idea why it would make that noise?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That intermittent clicking or static-y sound, especially when power is restored, suggests an electrical connection issue, possibly a loose wire or a failing contactor. It could also indicate that the motor is struggling to start due to an internal winding problem, which is a more serious issue. Before anything else, double-check every wire connection within the accessible panels, ensuring they are tight and properly seated. If the noise persists after confirming all connections are snug, the problem likely lies deeper within the motor or the control board.",
